HUGE', 'review_text': "It's a great phone but absolutely humongous and a pain to carry or use with one hand, and I have big hands. I am coming from an S10 which has served me incredibly well for the past 5 years but I wanted a bigger screen because my sight isn't what it used to be. I was between the Ultra and the plus and decided to go with the ultra for the snapdragon and the anti glare display, but now I regret not going with the regular 24 and saving 20K in the process. The gain in screen size, even compared to the standard S10, isn't that big of a deal and cannot justify the overall size and bulk.  I also hate the fact that they changed the UI navigation gestures, the new gestures are hit and miss but that applies to all S24 models.It was a good bundle deal from amazon though who generously threw in the original silicone case besides the galaxy buds fe and the free 2 year screen insurance samsung egypt offers early buyers. The free screen insurance is a little tricky to activate though. You need to log into your samsung members app, discover, tap the benefits tab and select the screen insurance, then manually register for it. The item listed here is the phone ONLY, if you are trying to buy the BUNDLE like I did, it's a different listing and will be clearly titled bundle. Phone and accessories were delivered together the same day. Delivery required a PIN as with all high value items. All items were sealed as expected from amazon, and the phone's warranty card was wedged in the box as usual. This is only for your own assurance, since from experience, you don't need the card for warranty claims as Samsung Egypt can look up the local warranty information if any with the phone's serial number.If you know exactly what you are getting and have used a recent ultra or note phone, go right ahead, you will not be disappointed aside from the new navigation gestures if you use them instead of the buttons like me; but if you are on the fence and trying to decide which S24 model to buy, I suggest you see them in person first. I know I would choose differently if I did. The anti reflective screen glass on the ultra really works but it also diffuses the pixel light and makes the display look a little bit like an LCD backlit display not an OLED. I really recommend you check out the phone in person first before dropping 66K on it. I am not happy with my purchase.
